B2C COMMERCE FOR MERCHANDISERS AND ADMINISTRATORS
Roles Managed in Account Manager

Use this table as a guide to the B2C Commerce Account Manager roles.

SERVICE NAME	ROLE NAME	TARGET TYPE	SCOPE OF ROLE	ALLOWED ACTIONS
Account Manager	Account Administrator	User/API Client	Organization	

Permits this user to view other user accounts. Permits this user to add other user accounts. Permits this user to edit other user accounts. Permits this user to edit API clients for their organization. Normally, only user accounts that belong to the same organization as the user are shown.

If a user with the Account Administrator role is assigned to multiple organizations, the user is the Account Administrator for all of the assigned organizations.


Account Manager	API Administrator	User/API Client	Organization	Permits the account to view API client IDs. Permits the account to add API client IDs. Permits the account to edit API client IDs. Enables the Account Manager API Client tab for the user.
Account Manager	Read Only Account Administrator	User/API Client	Organization	Permits the user read only access to the organization's details, API clients and users. Users with this role can't update or create organizations, API clients, or users.
Commerce Cloud Developer Experience	Sandbox API User	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits the user to manage on demand sandboxes (ODS) with the ODS REST API. It also provides a Control Center role to access and manage ODS in Control Center.
Commerce Cloud managed Runtime	Managed Runtime User	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Allows access to Commerce Runtime Manager as part of a specific organization.
Commerce Cloud Managed Runtime	Managed Runtime Administrator	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Allows admin access to Commerce Runtime Manager as part of a specific organization, allowing the admin to create projects and assign project permissions
Control Center	Control Center Administrator	User	For all Business Manager Instances	Permits the user to act as an administrator within their primary org. The user is granted administrative access to all instances of their primary organization in Control Center. Administrators can assign permissions to any instance of any realm in their organization to users in their own organization or another organization. This role allows Users to view audit logs, and to view users and manage roles in their primary org. See Control Center documentation for more details.
Control Center	Control Center User	User	For all Business Manager Instances	Permits use of the Control Center application. Users with this role can assign and unassign the permissions they received to an instance within Control Center (through direct assignment or role assignment). If the user has the Grant Permissions permission, they can assign the permission they received to other users assigned to the instance. See Control Center documentation for more details
CQuotient	CQuotient Configurator User	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits basic read and write access to individual sites.
eCommerce Platform and Business Manager	Business Manager Administrator	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits full administrative access to a Business Manager instance.
eCommerce Platform and Business Manager	Business Manager User	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits the user to log in to a Business Manager instance but doesn't automatically assign any BM roles beyond that. Administrators for the Business Manager instance can set up rules to assign some local roles upon a user's first login. See Business Manager documentation for more details.
Log Center	Log Center User	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits the user to access logs for a specific tenant and realms. Access to log messages is managed through tenant filters and Business Manager instances. Defining Business Manager instance for this role is mandatory. The role has access to the following Log Center features: log messages visualization, management of it's own save searches and notifications.
OCAPI Explorer	OCAPI Explorer Debug User	User	Tenant/Realm/Instance	Permits the user to access OCAPI request debug information on a per tenant, realm, and instance basis.
Reports and Dashboards (R&D)	Reports and Dashboards Customer Manager	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits the user to view the Reports and Dashboards for their realm and access the Reports and Dashboards settings page for their realm.
Reports and Dashboards (R&D)	Reports and Dashboards User	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits the user read only access to the Reports and dashboards for their realm.
Reports and Dashboards (R&D)	Reports and Dashboards Performance User	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits access to the Performance dashboard in R&D
SLAS Shopper Admin API	Salesforce Commerce API	API Client	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits the user to access the Salesforce Commerce APIs.
SLAS Shopper Admin API	SLAS Organization Administrator	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Assigns the Merchant role for management of SLAS tenant level configuration.
SLAS Shopper Admin API	SLAS Trusted Agent Read Only	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Assigns the Merchant role for use in Trusted Agent shopping flows (read only).
SLAS Shopper Admin API	SLAS Trusted Agent Read Write	User	Specific Business Manager Instance	Assigns the Merchant role for use in Trusted Agent shopping flows (read and write).
Commerce Cloud Developer Experience	Sandbox API User	User/API Client	Specific Business Manager Instance	Permits the user to create new on-demand sandboxes (ODS) using the REST API in AWS sandbox environment. This role also grants users access to ODS functionality within Control Center.
